15. DETAILED TECHNICAL SPECIFICATIONS (APPENDIX)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
15.1. Memory Management: Mandatory use of RAII and C++ smart pointers.
15.2. Logic Flow: cs.Update() must execute before cs.Draw() in all cycles.
15.3. Error Handling: Use of C++23 std::expected for all bridge calls.
15.4. Compilation: All projects must define _CUBEY_CORE_ during build.
15.5. Versioning: Minor engine updates do not require a license renewal.
15.6. Portability: Code must remain portable between Windows and Linux.
15.7. Optimization: Use of C++20 concepts is required for template safety.
15.8. Reflection: C++26 reflection hooks must be preserved for Lua bindings.
15.9. Audio: Use of the proprietary Codex-Audio wrapper is mandatory.
15.10. Physics: Integration with Codex-Physics must use the provided headers.
15.11. Networking: SSL/TLS is required for any networking component.
15.12. Input: Key-binding overrides must happen via the Director class.
15.13. Assets: .cubey file formats are proprietary and protected.
15.14. Documentation: All code must be documented using Doxygen format.
15.15. Testing: Mandatory unit testing for all PR submissions.
15.16. Deployment: Static linking is preferred for core modules.
15.17. Security: Buffer overflow checks must be enabled in release builds.
15.18. Performance: Frames-per-second must be capped via Director logic.
15.19. Legacy: No inclusion of C-style headers <stdio.h> allowed.
15.20. Modernity: Use of <iostream> is restricted to debug builds.

